Full Job Description:
Rockbell is expanding its team, and we are looking for a new candidate to join us on our journey!
Rockbell is a software company with specific focus in commercial accounting systems, and we are looking for a dedicated Software Programmer (which could be YOU!) to develop applications and implement more business solution options for our clients.
Why choose Rockbell?
We believe that our people are the foundation of our company!
We strive to constantly improve, and to ensure that our employees are properly equipped to handle the rapidly changing times we are in.
We are committed to building the right team to propel us further.
As part of our team at Rockbell and a Senior Programmer, you will be:-
Developing software applications and conducting backend works to ensure that our products are user-friendly and provide value to our customers;
Working together with other team members and departments to implement the most useful features;
Conducting maintenance and upgrading our software;
Ensuring that our software works as efficiently and smoothly as possible.
Identifying issues related to the coding of the programme and working in a team to develop fixes to those issues.
We are looking for someone who (preferably) is:-
At least 4 years’ working experience in a Programming Department of a company or with proven track record of software development;
Possesses a degree or diploma in Programming, IT or other related fields;
Fluent in English (fluency in Bahasa Malaysia and Bahasa Cina is a bonus!);
Dedicated to developing software and solutions that provide the most value to our clients;
Knowledgeable and has basic or strong proficiency in React and React Native (required);
Has knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript and prior experience with responsive and adaptive design (required);
Familiar with Electron, Expo, Node.js, PHP, MySQL & MicrosoftSQL databases (preferred);
Familiar with RESTful APIs, UI/UX Design, version control (Git) and React component library Material-UI (preferred);
Eager to learn and develop themselves!
If you are attracted to our prospects and want to join us without the necessary skills, please still apply!
Thank you for your interest in joining us. We might be overwhelmed with the response, and may only be able to reply to shortlisted candidates.

About the Role
Join MIYA GLOBAL TECHNOLOGY as a Junior Front-End Developer based in Kuala Lumpur. This full-time role is ideal for fresh graduates or entry-level candidates passionate about front-end development. You will be part of a collaborative team, contributing to the development and maintenance of web and mobile applications while gaining hands-on experience and growing your technical skills.
What You’ll Be Doing
Assist in developing and debugging web and mobile UI interfaces;
Support the creation and maintenance of reusable front-end components;
Work with product and design teams to enhance user experience and support product iterations;
Contribute to code quality improvements and performance optimization;
Continuously learn and apply new front-end technologies and best practices.
What We’re Looking For
Bachelor’s degree or above (Computer Science or related fields preferred); fresh graduates are welcome;
Solid understanding of computer science fundamentals and front-end development principles;
Basic knowledge of HTML, CSS, JavaScript; familiarity with frameworks like Vue or Svelte is a plus;
Strong willingness to learn and adapt to new technologies;
Good communication and teamwork skills;
Proactive attitude and problem-solving mindset;
Familiarity with development tools (e.g., VSCode, browser dev tools) is a plus;
Ability to read and understand technical documentation in English;
Proficiency in Mandarin is a plus, to support communication with Mandarin-speaking clients and team members.

Capital Dynamics is recruiting Front-End Developer to work with an energetic team in a fast-paced and entrepreneurial environment. Your responsibilities will include but not be limited to:
Building and maintaining a user-friendly website-browsing experience, solving various browser compatibility or other front-end problems;
Continuously optimising web architecture, web pages, and user experience (UX);
Researching front-end technical development and providing development structure relevant to project requirements.
Requirements:
At least a Bachelor's degree in IT or Computer Science;
The ability to accurately design CSS structure, and make pages that conform with w3c specifications;
Experience in developing apps using HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, JQuery, Bootstrap, AJAX, ReactJS, or AngularJS;
Experience in using Version Control System e.g. Git, SVN, etc;
Experience with RESTful web services design, development, and integration into web applications will be an advantage;
Proficient understanding of how to resolve cross-browser compatibility issues and optimise performance;
Knowledge of any one of the following but not limited to Python, Django, Node.js, and JAVA Spring will be at an advantage.
You should have an innovative and pioneering spirit, initiative, and a meticulous and responsible personality. Good communication skills and team spirit are also a must.
Fresh graduates are encouraged to apply.
